messages.content: Tell me about this dandiset. *

This Dandiset, titled “Hippocampal neuronal responses to programmable antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptor activation,” contains single-cell electrophysiological recordings from mouse hippocampal CA1 neurons. These neurons were transfected with a genetic construct allowing programmable antigen-gated G-protein-coupled engineered receptor (PAGER) expression. The responses were recorded under application of DCZ (a selective agonist) or DCZ combined with soluble mCherry.

Key details:

- Species: Mouse (Mus musculus)
- Area: Hippocampal CA1 neurons
- Technique: Current clamp electrophysiology (CurrentClampSeries and CurrentClampStimulusSeries)
- Data Standard: Neurodata Without Borders (NWB)
- Number of subjects: 8
- Number of cells: 50
- Number of files: 50 (each likely a cell recording)
- Use case: Assessment and validation of programmable antigen-gated GPCRs for targeted modulation of neuronal activity
- Associated publication: [Synthetic GPCRs for programmable sensing and control of cell behaviour](https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-024-08282-3)

You can browse the Dandiset and find downloadable NWB files on the DANDI Archive: [https://dandiarchive.org/dandiset/001354/0.250312.0036](https://dandiarchive.org/dandiset/001354/0.250312.0036)
